text: László Cseh (: born 3 December 1985, sometimes called Louis Czech in English- speaking countries) is a Hungarian competitive swimmer. He has won four silver Olympic medals and two bronze. He is a 33-time European Champion. His father, László Cseh Sr., also represented Hungary at the Olympics in swimming. ==References== Category:1985 births Category:Living people Category:Hungarian swimmers Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Hungary Category:Olympic silver medalists for Hungary Category:Sportspeople from Budapest
